    "## Results\n",
    "\n",
    "## Exploratory Data Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "## Data Source and Background\n",
    "\n",
    "This project uses data from the U.S. Census Bureau's Current Population Survey (CPS), specifically the **Computer and Internet Use Supplement (November 2023)**.  \n",
    "\n",
    "The survey collects information on household internet access, device ownership, and internet usage behavior across different locations.\n",
    "\n",
    "The dataset includes randomly selected respondents and records their demographic characteristics, labor force status, device ownership, and internet usage patterns.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Sample Structure\n",
    "\n",
    "After data cleaning, the dataset contains:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Observation unit:** individual (person-level)\n",
    "- **Sample size:** 37,047\n",
    "- **Number of variables:** 28\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key variables\n",
    "\n",
    "**Demographics**\n",
    "- age\n",
    "- sex\n",
    "- education\n",
    "- marital_status\n",
    "- race\n",
    "\n",
    "**Geographic information**\n",
    "- state_fips\n",
    "- metro_status\n",
    "- cbsa_code\n",
    "\n",
    "**Labor market**\n",
    "- labor_force_status_major\n",
    "- industry_major_recode\n",
    "- occupation_major_recode\n",
    "\n",
    "**Device ownership**\n",
    "- use_laptop\n",
    "- use_desktop\n",
    "- use_tablet\n",
    "- use_smartphone\n",
    "\n",
    "**Internet usage locations**\n",
    "- internet_at_home\n",
    "- internet_at_work\n",
    "- internet_at_school\n",
    "- internet_at_cafe\n",
    "- internet_while_traveling\n",
    "- internet_at_library_or_community\n",
    "- internet_elsewhere_home\n",
    "- internet_other_places\n",
    "\n",
    "**Indicators**\n",
    "- is_random_respondent\n",
    "- internet_user\n",
    "- internet_usage_count\n",
    "\n",
    "**Weight**\n",
    "- weight_person\n",
    "\n",
    "## Sampling Weights\n",
    "\n",
    "The CPS dataset provides a **final sampling weight (`weight_person`)**.\n",
    "\n",
    "This weight is used to produce population-representative estimates by adjusting for sampling design and demographic characteristics such as:\n",
    "\n",
    "- state\n",
    "- age\n",
    "- sex\n",
    "- race\n",
    "\n",
    "Therefore, descriptive statistics and group comparisons are reported both:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Unweighted** (sample distribution)\n",
    "- **Weighted** (population-adjusted estimates)\n",
    "\n",
    "## Special Codes\n",
    "\n",
    "In the CPS data system, the value **-1** is commonly used to represent:\n",
    "\n",
    "**\"Not in universe\"**\n",
    "\n",
    "This means that the question does not apply to the respondent.\n",
    "\n",
    "For example, in the marital status variable, the value **-1 may indicate \"No spouse\" or \"Not applicable\".**\n",
    "\n",
    "Therefore, these values are not missing data (NaN), but special coded responses that should be handled carefully during analysis."
