    "def _valid_series(x: pd.Series):\n",
    "    \"\"\"drop NaN and inf\"\"\"\n",
    "    x = x.replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan)\n",
    "    return x.dropna()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Weighted Mean Calculation\n",
    "\n",
    "Because the CPS dataset contains survey weights, we define a function\n",
    "to compute weighted means. This allows summary statistics to better\n",
    "represent the population rather than the raw sample."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 250,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def weighted_mean(x, w):\n",
    "    x = np.asarray(x, dtype=float)\n",
    "    w = np.asarray(w, dtype=float)\n",
    "\n",
    "    m = ~np.isnan(x)\n",
    "\n",
    "    if m.sum() == 0:\n",
    "        return np.nan\n",
    "\n",
    "    return (x[m] * w[m]).sum() / w[m].sum()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Numerical Summary Statistics\n",
    "\n",
    "This function generates descriptive statistics for numeric variables,\n",
    "including mean, standard deviation, median, and quartiles. When survey\n",
    "weights are available, weighted statistics are also calculated."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 251,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def describe_numeric(x: pd.Series, w: pd.Series | None = None):\n",
    "\n",
    "    x0 = _valid_series(x)\n",
    "\n",
    "    out = {\n",
    "        \"count\": int(x0.shape[0]),\n",
    "        \"mean\": float(x0.mean()) if len(x0) else np.nan,\n",
    "        \"std\": float(x0.std(ddof=1)) if len(x0) > 1 else np.nan,\n",
    "        \"min\": float(x0.min()) if len(x0) else np.nan,\n",
    "        \"p25\": float(x0.quantile(0.25)) if len(x0) else np.nan,\n",
    "        \"median\": float(x0.median()) if len(x0) else np.nan,\n",
    "        \"p75\": float(x0.quantile(0.75)) if len(x0) else np.nan,\n",
    "        \"max\": float(x0.max()) if len(x0) else np.nan,\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "    if w is not None:\n",
    "        w0 = w.loc[x0.index].astype(float)\n",
    "        out[\"w_mean\"] = float(weighted_mean(x0.values, w0.values))\n",
    "\n",
    "    return out"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Outlier Detection (IQR)\n",
    "\n",
    "This function identifies potential outliers using the\n",
    "interquartile range (IQR) method. Observations outside\n",
    "1.5 × IQR are flagged as potential outliers."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 252,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def iqr_outlier_mask(x: pd.Series):\n",
    "\n",
    "    x0 = _valid_series(x)\n",
    "\n",
    "    if len(x0) < 4:\n",
    "        return pd.Series(False, index=x.index)\n",
    "\n",
    "    q1 = x0.quantile(0.25)\n",
    "    q3 = x0.quantile(0.75)\n",
    "\n",
    "    iqr = q3 - q1\n",
    "\n",
    "    lo = q1 - 1.5 * iqr\n",
    "    hi = q3 + 1.5 * iqr\n",
    "\n",
    "    mask = (x < lo) | (x > hi)\n",
    "\n",
    "    return mask.fillna(False)"
   ]
  },
