    "* **Employment Rate:** The bar plot displays the employment probability across the two geographic areas. While the urban area shows a realistic employment rate with a 95% confidence interval, the rural group displays a 100% employment rate with no error bar. Rather than an economic anomaly, this is a statistical artifact: it indicates that in our small 1,000-row test subset, we have an extremely limited number of valid rural respondents after applying our age (25-54) and missing value filters.\n",
